      "message": "[error] Line 247: 🔴 Moving `decoder_` assignment after `sink_-\u003estart()`/`setFrameSize()` creates a callback window where daemon-managed `VideoInput` has no decoder. `getWidth()`/`getHeight()` still dereference `decoder_` unconditionally, so any client/sink notification during startup can crash. Snapshot the decoder values first, then assign `decoder_` before starting/signaling the sink, while keeping `playingFile_` and `loop_.start()` after setup.",
